:: Answer it {"position":"500,100","size":"100,100"}
You walk outside to the darkened street, glancing at the phone screen you cant quite seem to make out the number or name of whoever is calling you and you can't tell why... maybe a bug?
Nevertheless, you press accept and bring the phone up to your ear, giving a "hello?" as you do.

[[...->Ominous silence]]


:: Approach the door {"position":"3000,1100","size":"100,100"}
You continue to tell yourself it is nothing to worry about, nothing is here, it is just the old building shifting, or an animal, a rodent perhaps.

You take steps forward, readying yourself for anything ahead.
Your guy begins to tell you to get away from the darkness.
(if: $HasKnife)[The knife shakes within your grasp ever so slightly.]

[[Continue to approach]]

[[Back away down the corridor]]


:: Back away down the corridor {"position":"2800,1100","size":"100,100"}
You decide your better judgement is named as such for a good reason and begin to move backwards away from the door and around the bend, hoping that whatever caused the door to open isnt going to be a threat to your health.

You find yourself around the corner soon, giving a moments pause for any more noise; hearing nothing however, you turn around to view the cart ahead of you, feeling more confident that the door opening was merely the building shifting. Now that you think about it, its probably a good reason to get moving quicker.

[[Inspect the cart]]


:: Begin your travel {"position":"900,100","size":"100,100"}
You take a few steps down the street before your phone rings again.

This time you're frustrated and practically swipe the phone out of your pocket, but you're thankfully surprised to not see some odd or cryptic name, it instead reads "Mam <3".

You smile, the anxiety falling a little from this whole situation.

[[Pick up the phone]]


:: Beginning {"position":"100,100","size":"100,100"}
Far from home you sip a cup of coffee. The sun is setting and you feel... happy. 

Having taken a few days from home to spend some time to yourself, you find yourself in a small cafe as you enjoy your drink.

[[Sip your coffee]]


:: Collect yourself {"position":"3000,1300","size":"100,100"}
You uncoil your hand from around the bloodied knife, it now coated in a dark red stain, unnaturally dark, you try to compose yourself, to calm yourself down, but this whole situation is too bizarre, too sudden!

You stumble yourself along the corridor in a hurry, reaching the corner and turning it, pressing yourself against the wall and taking many deep breaths.

"What was that thing?", "A person?", "Was that even real?", "Am I going insane?"

You can't help but ask yourself this plethora of questions.

You need to get out of here as soon as possible.
Time to get to that cart, and fast.

[[Inspect the cart]]


:: Continue to approach {"position":"3200,1100","size":"100,100"}
You step forward once more, willing confidence into yourself.

Then you hear a creak... ABOVE YOU!!

You look up! Seeing... Something you cant even describe?! A creature? A man? It is distorted twisted, shrouded by the dark, so much so you didnt see it before.

You attempt to back away, you fell for its trap, but it grabs it's unnaturally clawed hands into you to pull you up!

(if:$HasKnife)[[Fight Back!->Stab the creature]]

(if:not$HasKnife)[[Fight Back!->Die to the creature]]




:: Die to the creature {"position":"3200,900","size":"100,100"}
You punch at the creature!!! Hitting its arms with all your might, but it's no use, it begins to lift you off the ground, its long rotten nails digging into your sides...

You kick! Strike!! Scream!!!
It is no use at all, you panic, your blood pools below you as it digs its claws deeper.

It screeches at you as it in turn uses its might to cleave you in twain, causing you to gasp your last breath before you feel as it pulls you into the dark, where you shall remain forevermore... 

The beloved star sets over the bitter ocean.

( You have died ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ )

[[Checkpoint!->Approach the door]]


:: Don't look away. {"position":"2600,1900","size":"100,100"}
You keep your eyes trained on the corner that turns left from behind. The steps may have stopped, but you still don't trust the silence.

You wait. The silence feels surprisingly deafening. Then amongst the silence, you hear another creak... above you.

You jolt your head up, and there! In the darkness above you! A creature? A man? It is distorted twisted, shrouded by the dark, so much so you didnt see it before.

You attempt to back away, you fell for its trap, but it grabs it's unnaturally clawed hands into you to pull you up!

[[Fight back!]]


:: Enter the maze {"position":"2800,1900","size":"100,100"}
You walk and walk and walk, turning corner after corner after corner. You feel panic setting in and tearing you apart.

Then finally! Thankfully! The T junction!
You pick up your pace, finally turning left, expecting the small hall leading to the staff door you entered through, but instead you are faced with a long and dark corridor. It carries on into the darkness, even more corridors branching off to the sides.

You wonder briefly if it is wise to traverse this new area, perhaps it is smarter to turn back. This thought is very quickly cut short as you hear the noise of what sounds like metal sheering, and what sounds like a screech camoflauged within it.

(if:$EncounteredEarly)[You recognise it, that thing is back! It mustve just broken through one of the many doors back down the corridors. Your heart feels like it is about to jump out of your chest, you got lucky in the first encounter with it, it underestimated you, it may not end the same way this time.]
(if:not$EncounteredEarly)[It is an incredibly unsettling noise, and it definitely doesn't sound like a rodent or animal youve ever heard of. 
You hold incredibly still, then you hear it; step, step, step. Whatever it is is coming. (if:$HasKnife)[You flick out the pocket knife and grip it firmly in your hand.]You brace yourself, but then the steps stop, has it stopped it's approach?]

(if:$EncounteredEarly)[[Run down the corridors.]]
(if:not$EncounteredEarly)[[Don't look away.]]


:: Fail to turn back. {"position":"2800,2400","size":"100,100"}
You turn on your heel and head back to the crossroads. If you're gonna make it out of here, you need to be fast!

You reach it! You try to head down the opposite corridor, but a little too late you see the creature beside you, it had caught up. You try to evade it, but it charges you, knocking you to your feet, clambering over you and digging its claws into you.

The wounds burn, you push and push to get it off, but it tears you apart, your fighting becomes weaker and weaker until you can't fight back anymore, giving in to your wounds.

The beloved star sets over the bitter ocean.

( You died! ¯\_(ツ)_/¯ )

